rComments: The course content was really fun and interesting, Professor Narine did a great job helping us understand the material in such a short period of time due to the fact it was a accelerated course in the summer. If you do the readings, study/understand the lectures, and participate in class, you won't get below a 80.

rComments: Prof Narine was amazing! He made sure to tell us everything we need to study so there were no surprises in the exams. He is a really nice guy, he cares about his students a lot. He always tried to help the best he could. Exams were fair, study all the bold terms from the textbook and exams were noncumulative. Overall, I really enjoyed this course!
